news.title: UK brings in ownership register for property held by foreign companies
news.para: The "Register of Overseas Entities", which becomes active from Monday, is part of a wider economic crime law enacted this year in an effort to stop the flow of illicit Russian cash into London following Moscow's invasion of Ukraine.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of Mega Mould, Remac Realty on Aug 18
news.para: ​It will auction a total of four properties of these two firms for a reserve price totalling Rs 4.05 crore, according to a public notice issued by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi).

news.title: China Evergrande Group's unit ordered to pay $1.1 billion
news.para: Evergrande Nanchang had provided counter-guarantees in the form of a pledge of 1.3 billion shares in Shengjing Bank that it held, according to the filing.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance aims to double affordable housing business in next few years
news.para: ​The housing finance company added over 100 branches across Andhra Pradesh, Telangana, Tamil Nadu, Maharashtra, Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan, Karnataka, Gujarat, Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh on August 1, 2022, IIFL HFL said in a release.

news.title: Ramco Cements' net profit down 36.4% at Rs 109.23 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its total income rose 44 per cent to 1,785.64 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 1,240 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board survey of flats continues
news.para: Since there are 18,516 small flats across the city allotted under different rehabilitation schemes, the authority will check all these flats in a phased manner, every Sunday.

news.title: ICICI Bank raises lending rate by 15 bps
news.para: Indiabulls Housing Finance Ltd (IBHFL) also hiked its reference rates on housing loans and MSME loans by 25 basis points in line with other players.

news.title: Cement volumes are expected to grow by 7-8% in FY23: ICRA
news.para: Elevated input costs are likely to result in a decline in operating profit margins of cement companies by 440-490 bps in FY23, according to ICRA.

news.title: Environmentalists say Rs 433 crore fine on illegal brick kiln units in Thadagam too little
news.para: The report, submitted on July 20, said that 1.1 crore cubic metres of brick earth was illegally mined and transported from 565 fields in Thadagam.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires land for a residential project in Mumbai
news.para: In a separate release, Godrej Properties said that ICRA had upgraded its long term borrowing programs.

news.title: Corporation plans to cancel detailed town planning schemes in Thiruvananthapuram
news.para: ​The matter was included in the agenda of the council meeting held on July 14, which apparently was declared as passed amid the din. No discussion was held on the cancellation of DTP schemes in the city during the council meeting.

news.title: Mumbai: Nodal officers to ensure housing societies learn fire safety drill
news.para: The officer will also have to ensure that societies in coordination with designated associations and fire brigades hold training for their members in handling contingency situations, including how to douse a fire and evacuate residents.

news.title: Indore: Survey identifies 80,000 property tax irregularities
news.para: Owners of these propers declared less than the actual planning area of their respective properties in the self-declaration while obtaining building permission, said officials.

news.title: Gandhinagar development body to auction three plots in Kudasan, Sargasan, Vavol
news.para: The plots are in town planning schemes 6, 7 and 13. In the case of the plot in Kudasan, GUDA has fixed a base price of Rs 73,000 per sq m and is expected to yield Rs 40.43 crore.

news.title: DLF cuts net debt by 16% quarter-on-quarter to Rs 2,259 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: On the operational front, DLF's sales bookings doubled to Rs 2,040 crore during the first quarter of this fiscal from Rs 1,014 crore in the year-ago period.
